reviews.review:
comboluted, safe, bland, nonsensical, predictable are some of the adjetives I would use to describe this movie, I won't lie that the visual effects were on point, the movie didn't look bad at all, but at the service of what? if the last jedi was the "subvert your expectations" queen TROS is the complete opposite, an expercience that will be so predictable to anyone from the moment they  read the first paragraph of the title crawl. 
A shame 36 years transpired for an "official" sequel to a beloved story and this is what we get...
The best way to end the saga!

This was the worst film made by Disney in regards to the Star Wars trilogy’s films. I thought The Last Jedi directed by Rian Johnson, was distasteful and made no sense, but this train wreck directed by JJ Abrams, was an abomination to the Star Wars saga. You just never connect to any of the main characters because the editing and the bad overacting never gives you a chance to. The ending of this muck movie will make you walk out the theater with a migraine and ask  yourself. Why in the hell was this movie ever made?
So much better than the previous film. My only complaint is there was a lot going on the entire time.
I absolutely loved it! Everything I hoped it would be. A beautiful final chapter.

Overwhelmingly fast paced, terrible dialogue, full of exposition, and complete destruction of major character arcs (finn, rey, rose????). the forced nostalgia fest felt cheap and lazy and contributed nothing to the overall story. what was the theme???? there was none. rey and ben's scenes were the only thing keeping this movie together.
A good close to a story generations in the making. There's a lot going on so my biggest complaint is that I'm going to have to watch it again...darn!

Very, very good, not amazing. Hey, it’s Star Wars, so has to be good!  Great action, maybe could have slowed down a little at times. Great acting, Adam Driver and Daisy Ridley are awesome. Realistic effects, much better than the prequels. Spoiler alert (kind of): not sure I loved the Emperor’s return, something there felt a little...off. Overall fun and, at times, touching. Enjoy. MTFBWY!
I'm very pleased with the movie and story.  There are always different directions things could go, but the outcome is great. Onward to new adventures!
It was a very good film! Definitely the best episode of the last trilogy! It’s a lot to consume and there are plot issues but it wraps up the whole saga well!
